parameters.text:
=Analyze this email and decide if it needs an automated reply.

From: {{ $json.from || $json.From }}
Subject: {{ $json.subject || $json.Subject }}
Body: {{ $json.text || $json.snippet || '(no body)' }}

Respond ONLY with this JSON (no markdown, no explanation):
{"should_reply": boolean, "type": "customer_inquiry|support_request|faq|client_reply|spam|newsletter|automated|other", "tone": "professional|friendly|formal", "sentiment": "positive|neutral|negative|urgent", "confidence": 0.0-1.0, "reason": "brief reason"}

parameters.jsCode:
const input = $input.first().json;
const email = $node['New Email'].json;

// AI Agent failed — flag for manual review
if (input.error) {
  return [{
    json: {
      should_reply: false,
      type: 'error',
      tone: 'professional',
      confidence: 0,
      reason: 'AI triage failed: ' + (input.error.message || 'Unknown error'),
      needs_manual_review: true,
      email_from: email.from,
      email_subject: email.subject,
      email_body: email.text || email.snippet || '',
      email_message_id: email.id,
      email_thread_id: email.threadId
    }
  }];
}

// Strip markdown code blocks (Gemini sometimes wraps in ```json)
const cleaned = (input.output || '').replace(/```json?\n?/gi, '').replace(/```/g, '').trim();

let decision;
try {
  const match = cleaned.match(/\{[\s\S]*\}/);
  if (!match) throw new Error('No JSON in agent output');
  decision = JSON.parse(match[0]);
} catch (e) {
  decision = { should_reply: false, type: 'parse_error', tone: 'professional', confidence: 0, reason: 'Parse error: ' + e.message };
}

return [{
  json: {
    should_reply: decision.should_reply === true,
    type: decision.type || 'other',
    tone: decision.tone || 'professional',
    confidence: parseFloat(decision.confidence) || 0,
    reason: decision.reason || '',
    needs_manual_review: false,
    sentiment: decision.sentiment || 'neutral',
    email_from: email.from,
    email_subject: email.subject,
    email_body: email.text || email.snippet || '',
    email_message_id: email.id,
    email_thread_id: email.threadId
  }
}];

parameters.text:
=Write a {{ $json.tone }} email reply in under 120 words.

Sentiment detected: {{ $json.sentiment }}
Tone adjustment rules:
- If sentiment is "negative" → respond calmly and apologetically, acknowledge their frustration
- If sentiment is "urgent" → acknowledge the urgency directly and be concise
- If sentiment is "positive" → match their energy, be warm
- If sentiment is "neutral" → stay professional and helpful

Original Email:
From: {{ $json.email_from }}
Subject: {{ $json.email_subject }}
Message: {{ $json.email_body }}

Write ONLY the reply body. No subject line. No headers. No placeholders.
